snippet.textDisplay: Never go by the shape of a snakes head to tell if it's poisonous!   The bellies of poisonous snakes have broken patterns that don't  repeat!  Also the tail is far more important than the head is,  Poisonous snakes have large middle sections that go blunt or taper really fast in a short span of a few inches.. 6 or there about,  A none poisonous snakes will taper off very slow over a long range!  Them fast blunted tails are a good sign it's poisonous!  The head being Diamond shaped is a horrible way to determine if it's dangerous or not,  Velvet tailed rattlers will fool you!  Cotton mouth can fool you also until they get mad!  The tail and belly is a fast way to Judge with certainty...
